        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>As in all isopods the eggs are incubated in a marsupial chamber between the walking legs of females and emerge as fully-formed juveniles.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_573",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>A second smaller and smooth bodied species <i>T. capensis</i>, if found from Cape Point Eastwards to about Port Elizabeth but the ranges of the two species do not overlap. Unlikely to be confused with any other regional isopods due to its large size and unusual habits.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_574",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
